{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "At Meta, the APR system is connected to the internal code review platform (Marginean et al. 2019); at Bloomberg, Kirbas et al. (2021) write that \"Bloomberg's view was that full automation was far from ideal\", and they subject APR patches to be reviewed by a software engineer.",
    "This is also reflected in Noller et al. 's results that \"full developer trust requires a manual patch review\".",
    "A promising way to present developers with explanations could be to show the reasoning trace (Lim et al. 2009) of a tool, i.e.",
    "how an automated debugging tool came to recommend a certain line for FL or a certain patch for APR.",
    "Unlike post-hoc explanation techniques such as commit message generation (Jiang et al. 2017), reasoning traces can answer critical questions that a developer may have, such as 'why this patch?"
  ],
